---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import comparison from '../../../proof/select/comparison.json';
const rows=[
 ['Immutable TypeScript control','passed control','Selected browser-backed receipts across four frameworks','Package 2.5.2: 7,986 B runtime chunk; 10,698 B principal types'],
 ['Shared-core native Select','failed','8/8 model contract; Solid has four observed browser failures; React/Vue/Svelte browser gates blocked','41 shared LOC + 43/79/180/69 native LOC'],
 ['Mitosis Select','partial','Generation/provenance only; behavior, SSR/hydration, types/package/styles not-run','400/488/336/517 B generated target sources']
];
---
<Layout title="Select pilot · Kumo">
<header><p class="eyebrow"><a href="/bakeoff/">Bake-off</a> / Select</p><h1>Select pilot: evidence, not a winner</h1><p>Three implementations have unequal scope. Contract, structural, browser, and blocked evidence are reported separately.</p></header>
<aside><strong>No winner is declared.</strong> Shared-core’s receipt is fail-closed: {comparison.sharedCore.gateCounts.passed} passed, {comparison.sharedCore.gateCounts.failed} failed, {comparison.sharedCore.gateCounts.blocked} blocked.</aside>
<section><h2>Comparison</h2><div class="table" tabindex="0" role="region" aria-label="Select implementation comparison; scroll horizontally on smaller screens"><table><thead><tr><th>Candidate</th><th>Status</th><th>Public behavior / SSR-hydration</th><th>Ownership and bytes</th></tr></thead><tbody>{rows.map(r=><tr>{r.map(c=><td>{c}</td>)}</tr>)}</tbody></table></div><p>Package/source byte counts are provenance facts, not equivalent bundle or product-scope measurements.</p></section>
<section class="cards"><article><h2>Contract ≠ browser</h2><strong>8/8</strong><p>Shared model contract vectors passed. Vue and Solid structural builds and SSR passed.</p></article><article><h2>Observed Solid failures</h2><strong>4</strong><p>Pointer open/select, typeahead, controlled state, and hydration actually failed.</p></article><article><h2>Blocked targets</h2><strong>3</strong><p>React, Vue, and Svelte browser gates are blocked by integration/harness failures—not behavior passes.</p></article><article><h2>Consumer DX</h2><strong>3 / 22 / 6</strong><p>Passed / blocked / not-run. The three passes are tarball packing only.</p></article></section>
<section><h2>Native boundaries and maintenance</h2><p>Shared-core retains target-owned rendering, reactivity, events, focus/scroll and SSR/hydration integration, plus three harness adapter files per framework. Upstream changes can touch the model, four views, and proof adapters. Mitosis uses a generator API adapter and has not run Select package, type, style, behavior or hydration gates.</p></section>
<section class="next"><h2>Pilot verdict</h2><p>Repair Select evidence and product gaps before Dialog. Dialog may proceed only as a bounded contract experiment—not a parity campaign.</p><p><a href="/shared-core/">Shared-core details</a> · <a href="/bakeoff/">Architecture matrix</a></p></section>
</Layout>
<style>header{max-width:900px;padding:32px 0 12px}h1{font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);margin:8px 0;letter-spacing:-.04em}header>p:last-child,section p{color:#475569;line-height:1.65}.eyebrow{font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}aside,.next{margin:24px 0;padding:18px 20px;border-left:4px solid #d97706;background:#fffbeb}section{margin:38px 0}.table{display:block;width:100%;max-width:100%;overflow:auto;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px}table{width:100%;min-width:820px;border-collapse:collapse;background:white}th,td{padding:12px;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;font-size:13px}.cards{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:12px}.cards article{border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px;padding:18px}.cards strong{font-size:28px}@media(max-width:650px){.cards{grid-template-columns:1fr}}</style>
